[
    {
        "speaker": "Polonius",
        "text": [
            "How now, Ophelia, what's",
            "the matter?"
        ]
    },
    {
        "speaker": "Ophelia",
        "text": [
            "O, my lord, my lord,",
            "I have been so affrighted."
        ]
    },
    {
        "speaker": "Polonius",
        "text": [
            "With what, i'th'name of God?"
        ]
    },
    {
        "speaker": "Ophelia",
        "text": [
            "My lord, as I was sewing in my",
            "closet, Lord Hamlet, with his",
            "doublet all unbraced,"
        ]
    },
    {
        "speaker": "Ophelia",
        "text": [
            "and with a look so piteous in",
            "purport as if he had been loosed",
            "out of hell to speak of horrors,"
        ]
    },
        {
        "speaker": "Ophelia",
        "text": [
            "he comes before me."
        ]
    },
    {
        "speaker": "Polonius",
        "text": [
            "Mad for thy love?"
        ]
    },
    {
        "speaker": "Ophelia",
        "text": [
            "My lord, I do not know, but",
            "truly I do fear it."
        ]
    },
    {
        "speaker": "Polonius",
        "text": [
            "What said he?"
        ]
    },
    {
        "speaker": "Ophelia",
        "text": [
            "He took my by the wrist and",
            "held me hard. Then goes he",
            "to the length of all his arm,"
        ]
    },
    {
        "speaker": "Ophelia",
        "text": [
            "And, with his other hand thus",
            "o'er his brow, he falls to",
            "such perusal of my face"
        ]
    },
    {
        "speaker": "Ophelia",
        "text": [
            "As he would draw it.",
            "Long stayed he so."
        ]
    },
    {
        "speaker": "Ophelia",
        "text": [
            "At last, a little shaking of",
            "mine arm, and thrice his head",
            "thus waving up and down,"
        ]
    },
    {
        "speaker": "Ophelia",
        "text": [
            "He raised a sigh so piteous",
            "and profound as it did seem",
            "to shatter all his bulk"
        ]
    },
    {
        "speaker": "Ophelia",
        "text": [
            "And end his being."
        ]
    },
    {
        "speaker": "Polonius",
        "text": [
            "Come, go with me. I will go seek",
            "the King. This is the very",
            "ecstasy of love, whose violent"
        ]
    },
    {
        "speaker": "Polonius",
        "text": [
            "property fordoes itself and",
            "leads the will to desperate",
            "undertakings as oft as any"
        ]
    },
    {
        "speaker": "Polonius",
        "text": [
            "passions under heaven that",
            "does afflict our natures.",
            "I am sorry."
        ]
    },
    {
        "speaker": "Polonius",
        "text": [
            "What, have you given him any",
            "hard words of late?"
        ]
    },
    {
        "speaker": "Ophelia",
        "text": [
            "No, my good lord, but as you did",
            "command I did repel his letters",
            "and denied his access to me."
        ]
    },
    {
        "speaker": "Polonius",
        "text": [
            "That hath made him mad.",
            "Come, go we to the King. This",
            "must be known, which, being"
        ]
    },
    {
        "speaker": "Polonius",
        "text": [
            "kept close, might move more",
            "grief to hide than hate to utter",
            "love."
        ]
    },
    {
        "speaker": "Polonius",
        "text": [
            "Come."
        ]
    }
]